Pakistan Weighs Strike Against Taliban Over Airport Attack
An attack on Karachi's Jinnah International Airport on Sunday night killed at least 28 people. The extremist Pakistani Taliban said the assault was pay-back for recent military airstrikes against them. (Photo: Zuma Press)
